4585 /**
4586  * @brief sends 72 clock pulses to the LTC daisy-chain.
4587  *
4588  * This function is used for the communication with the multiplexers via I2C on the GPIOs.
4589  * It send the command STCOMM to the LTC daisy-chain.
4590  *
4591  * @param pSpiInterface pointer to SPI configuration
4592  *
4593  * @return statusSPI #STD_OK if clock pulses were sent correctly by SPI, #STD_NOT_OK otherwise
4594  *
4595  */
4596 static STD_RETURN_TYPE_e LTC_I2cClock(SPI_INTERFACE_CONFIG_s *pSpiInterface) {
4597  FAS_ASSERT(pSpiInterface != NULL_PTR);
4598  STD_RETURN_TYPE_e statusSPI = STD_NOT_OK;
4599  uint16_t ltc_TXBufferClock[4u + 9u];
4600 
4601  for (uint16_t i = 0; i < (4u + 9u); i++) {
4602  ltc_TXBufferClock[i] = 0xFF;
4603  }
4604 
4605  ltc_TXBufferClock[0] = ltc_cmdSTCOMM[0];
4606  ltc_TXBufferClock[1] = ltc_cmdSTCOMM[1];
4607  ltc_TXBufferClock[2] = ltc_cmdSTCOMM[2];
4608  ltc_TXBufferClock[3] = ltc_cmdSTCOMM[3];
4609 
4610  statusSPI = LTC_TRANSMIT_I2C_COMMAND(pSpiInterface, ltc_TXBufferClock);
4611 
4612  return statusSPI;
4613 }
4614 
4615 /**
4616  * @brief gets the frequency of the SPI clock.
4617  *
4618  * This function reads the configuration from the SPI handle directly.
4619  *
4620  * @param pSpiInterface pointer to SPI configuration
4621  *
4622  * @return frequency of the SPI clock
4623  */
4624 static uint32_t LTC_GetSpiClock(SPI_INTERFACE_CONFIG_s *pSpiInterface) {
4625  FAS_ASSERT(pSpiInterface != NULL_PTR);
4626  uint32_t SPI_Clock = 0;
4627  uint32_t prescaler = 0;
4628 
4629  /* if (LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI2 || LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI3) { */
4630  /* SPI2 and SPI3 are connected to APB1 (PCLK1) */
4631  /* The prescaler setup bits LTC_SPI_PRESCALER corresponds to the bits 5:3 in the SPI_CR1 register */
4632  /* Reference manual p.909 */
4633  /* The shift by 3 puts the bits 5:3 to the first position */
4634  /* Division are made by powers of 2 which corresponds to shifting to the right */
4635  /* Then 0 corresponds to divide by 2, 1 corresponds to divide by 4... so 1 has to be added to the value of the configuration bits */
4636 
4637  /* SPI_Clock = HAL_RCC_GetPCLK1Freq()>>((LTC_SPI_PRESCALER>>3)+1);
4638  } */
4639 
4640  /* if (LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI1 || LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI4 || LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI5 || LTC_SPI_INSTANCE == SPI6) { */
4641  /* SPI1, SPI4, SPI5 and SPI6 are connected to APB2 (PCLK2) */
4642  /* The prescaler setup bits LTC_SPI_PRESCALER corresponds to the bits 5:3 in the SPI_CR1 register */
4643  /* Reference manual p.909 */
4644  /* The shift by 3 puts the bits 5:3 to the first position */
4645  /* Division are made by powers of 2 which corresponds to shifting to the right */
4646  /* Then 0 corresponds to divide by 2, 1 corresponds to divide by 4... so 1 has to be added to the value of the configuration bits */
4647 
4648  /* SPI_Clock = HAL_RCC_GetPCLK2Freq()>>((LTC_SPI_PRESCALER>>3)+1);
4649  } */
4650 
4651  /* Get SPI prescaler */
4652  prescaler = ((pSpiInterface->pNode->FMT0) >> 8u) & 0xFFu;
4653  SPI_Clock = (uint32_t)(AVCLK1_FREQ * 1000000u) / (prescaler + 1u);
4654 
4655  return SPI_Clock;
4656 }
4657 
4658 /**
4659  * @brief sets the transfer time needed to receive/send data with the LTC daisy-chain.
4660  *
4661  * This function gets the clock frequency and uses the number of LTCs in the daisy-chain.
4662  *
4663  * @param ltc_state: state of the ltc state machine
4664  *
4665  */
4666 static void LTC_SetTransferTimes(LTC_STATE_s *ltc_state) {
4667  FAS_ASSERT(ltc_state != NULL_PTR);
4668  uint32_t transferTime_us = 0;
4669  uint32_t SPI_Clock = 0;
4670 
4671  SPI_Clock = LTC_GetSpiClock(ltc_state->ltcData.pSpiInterface);
4672 
4673  /* Transmission of a command and data */
4674  /* Multiplication by 1000*1000 to get us */
4675  transferTime_us = (8u * 1000u * 1000u) / (SPI_Clock);
4676  transferTime_us *= LTC_N_BYTES_FOR_DATA_TRANSMISSION;
4677  transferTime_us = transferTime_us + LTC_SPI_WAKEUP_WAIT_TIME_US;
4678  ltc_state->commandDataTransferTime = (transferTime_us / 1000u) + 1u;
4679 
4680  /* Transmission of a command */
4681  /* Multiplication by 1000*1000 to get us */
4682  transferTime_us = ((4u) * 8u * 1000u * 1000u) / (SPI_Clock);
4683  transferTime_us = transferTime_us + LTC_SPI_WAKEUP_WAIT_TIME_US;
4684  ltc_state->commandTransferTime = (transferTime_us / 1000u) + 1u;
4685 
4686  /* Transmission of a command + 9 clocks */
4687  /* Multiplication by 1000*1000 to get us */
4688  transferTime_us = ((4u + 9u) * 8u * 1000u * 1000u) / (SPI_Clock);
4689  transferTime_us = transferTime_us + LTC_SPI_WAKEUP_WAIT_TIME_US;
4690  ltc_state->gpioClocksTransferTime = (transferTime_us / 1000u) + 1u;
4691 }

4693 /**
4694  * @brief checks the state requests that are made.
4695  *
4696  * This function checks the validity of the state requests.
4697  * The results of the checked is returned immediately.
4698  *
4699  * @param ltc_state: state of the ltc state machine
4700  * @param statereq state request to be checked
4701  *
4702  * @return result of the state request that was made, taken from LTC_RETURN_TYPE_e
4703  */
4704 static LTC_RETURN_TYPE_e LTC_CheckStateRequest(LTC_STATE_s *ltc_state, LTC_REQUEST_s statereq) {
4705  FAS_ASSERT(ltc_state != NULL_PTR);
4706  LTC_RETURN_TYPE_e retVal = LTC_OK;
4707  if (statereq.string >= BS_NR_OF_STRINGS) {
4708  retVal = LTC_ILLEGAL_REQUEST;
4709  } else if (ltc_state->statereq.request == LTC_STATE_NO_REQUEST) {
4710  /* init only allowed from the uninitialized state */
4711  if (statereq.request == LTC_STATE_INIT_REQUEST) {
4712  if (ltc_state->state == LTC_STATEMACH_UNINITIALIZED) {
4713  retVal = LTC_OK;
4714  } else {
4715  retVal = LTC_ALREADY_INITIALIZED;
4716  }
4717  } else {
4718  retVal = LTC_OK;
4719  }
4720  } else {
4721  retVal = LTC_REQUEST_PENDING;
4722  }
4723 
4724  return retVal;
4725 }

4731  OS_EnterTaskCritical();
4732  retval = ltc_state->first_measurement_made;
4733  OS_ExitTaskCritical();
4734 
4735  return (retval);
4736 }
